I am aware that this is not the first time I have been involved in speeding incidents, and I acknowledge the penalty points on my license from previous offenses. However, this offense is the first one that has resulted in legal proceedings. Despite this, I want to assure the court that I do not have a criminal record beyond the driving offenses.

Furthermore, I have recently been diagnosed with ADHD, which may have influenced my impulsive decision-making in this instance. While this does not excuse my conduct, it is a factor that should be taken into consideration when determining an appropriate penalty. I am actively seeking treatment and taking steps to manage my condition better.

I want to emphasize that I am genuinely remorseful for my actions and the potential harm caused. I have taken this incident as a wake-up call and am committed to making amends for my behavior. I am willing to undergo any necessary training or counseling to address the underlying issues that led to this offense. 

In conclusion, Your Honor, I plead guilty for my involvement in the offense. I understand the gravity of my actions and the need for appropriate consequences. I ask for leniency and an opportunity to rehabilitate myself, so that I may learn from this experience and prevent the same offense from occurring again in the future.

